<h4 id="org7365379">Ubiquitous Dataset Abstraction</h4>
<p>
Load a <a href="https://docs.pytorch.org/tutorials/beginner/basics/data_tutorial.html#creating-a-custom-dataset-for-your-files">custom Pytorch Dataset</a> no matter where/how the samples are stored.
</p>

<ul>
<li class="fragment appear visible" data-fragment-index="0">Just needs the length calculation and the <span class="underline"><span class="underline">iter</span></span> functionality</li>
<li class="fragment appear visible current-fragment" data-fragment-index="1">Inherits pytorch Dataset class as parent so it's automatically compatible with pytorch</li>

</ul>

<div class="org-src-container">

